Mini Chip.description: For the notifications that are in the navigation

subtle-2x.description: For light surface contrasts, such as in My List row items where there is surface on surface, usually one is white over the subtle 2x.

placeholder.description: For text placeholders inside fileds. Mostly for search fields.

subtle-2x.description: For darker items like icons in buttons with or without text

subtle-3x.description: For contrast against text. For icons fills/borders. It's also used coupled with a list item text. See Inputs Dropdown for examples.

strong.description: For important text instances colors, list items, table cell texts,  in resting state.

strongest.description: For important text instances colors, list items, table cell texts, table headers, titles, in hover and selected states.

default.description: Border used mostly for gray buttons.

subtle-1x.description: Border used mostly for dividers of sections and tables.

focused.description: Similar to effects token theme/shadow/Focused/default, this is for strokes on focused state items that were initially created with a border instead of the shadow effect.

subtle-2x.description: For light surface contrasts, such as in My List row items where there is surface on surface, usually one is white over the subtle 2x.

field.description: Dark color for fields to have a slight contracts against other surfaces.

placeholder.description: For text placeholders inside fileds. Mostly for search fields.

subtle-3x.description: For contrast against text. For icons fills/borders. It's also used coupled with a list item text. See Inputs Dropdown for examples.

strong.description: For text of inputs and buttons in resting state.

default.description: Border used mostly for gray buttons.

subtle-1x.description: Border used mostly for dividers of sections and tables. Can also be used for disabled borders on all items. Corresponding disabled token for surfaces is theme/fg/disabled.

disabled.description: For disabled borders on all items. For disabled fill use the corresponding disabled token for surfaces is theme/fg/disabled.

focused.description: Similar to effects token theme/shadow/Focused/default, this is for strokes on focused state items that were initially created with a border instead of the shadow effect.
